        "username": "Howard_Cooper",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/howard_cooper/{size}/700_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-12-10T12:53:43.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks Michael.  I have bought the 2017 Cardeuse but have not tried it yet.  I did have a Ramonet CM villages 2017 rouge last night during the zoom with William Kelley.  The wine started off pretty tight and a bit harsh, but really opened up during the course of the zoom call and really became wonderful - Williams did a wonderful job from the start and never was close to being harsh.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\"></p>\n<p>You and Don really seem to have started this push for Chassagne red and I certainly am a disciple.  Love the wines, although I must admit I have not gone beyond these two producers.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/d/df165fe9c1593d19166ae7e1ffe5e272089cc07b.gif\" width=\"50\" height=\"37\" alt=\"[thankyou.gif]\" title=\"thankyou\">  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/9/99a8907a1d5b3c023582052741dc72dc9823c044.gif\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" alt=\"[worship.gif]\" title=\"worship\"></p>",
        "post_number": 4,
        "post_type": 1,
